<T>__{go to black:}
<L>__{interior mandela's bedroom night}
<A>__{dark. we can make out the form of a tall man sleeping alone at the very edge of the big bed, as if not wanting to rumple the blankets too much. on the bedside table, the clock clicks from 4:59 to 5:00. the man's eyes open in the dark, instantly awake. he reaches out, switches on the light. nelson rolihlahla mandela, 76, sits up and gets out of bed in one movement. he has the physical vigor and energy of someone twenty years younger. the second he is up, he turns around and makes his bed, leaving it as flawlessly smooth as a hospital bed. or a prison bunk. for this is the discipline of twenty seven years behind bars.}
